Prep the ingredients: Halve, peel, and finely chop the @yellow onion{1}. Core, seed, and remove the white ribs from the @red bell pepper{1}, then finely dice. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Drain and rinse the @black beans{13.4%ounce}. Pick the @oregano{1/4%ounce} leaves off the stem and roughly chop.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium heat. Add the onion and bell pepper and cook, tossing, for ~{5-6%minutes}, until very soft. Add the garlic, oregano, @cumin{1%tsp}, and @chili powder{1%tsp} and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Add the beans and @diced tomatoes{14%ounce} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer for about ~{15%minutes}, until thickened. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If you have more time, feel free to let the chili simmer for longer!

Plate and garnish the chili: Divide the chili between bowls, then top with @sour cream{1%ounce}, @cheddar cheese{2%ounce}, and Enjoy!